<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>Body Builder Electrical Data Book - CF 500, CF 600 Rear Axle - Rear Drive Axle/Differential - Dana S110 -
        In-Vehicle Repair
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="remove" graphiccount="20">
        <title>In-Vehicle Repair</title>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Differential Carrier Removal</title>
            <specpara>
                <warning>
                    <para>Do not use heat when disassembling a drive axle. To do so will destroy heat treat properties
                        and weaken or distort axle components. Failure to follow these instructions may result in
                        personal injury.
                    </para>
                </warning>
            </specpara>
            <specpara>
                <caution>
                    <para>Steam clean the axle prior to removal from the vehicle. Dirt is abrasive and will cause
                        premature wear of otherwise usable components.
                    </para>
                </caution>
            </specpara>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Steam clean the axle assembly.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Set the parking brake.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Chock the wheels.</para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f0502A03" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figDE1/DE1889A.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         scalefitheight="232px"/>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Drain the axle lubricant into a suitable container.</para>
                <randlist type="bullet">
                    <item>
                        <para>Remove the bottom 2 carrier bolts and drain the assembly.</para>
                    </item>
                </randlist>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f0502A04" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figA00/A0062249.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         scalefitheight="232px"/>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Disconnect the rear anti-lock brake sensor electrical connector, if equipped.</para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f0502A05" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figDE1/DE1891A.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         scalefitheight="232px"/>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Index-mark the driveshaft so it can be reinstalled in its original position to maintain
                    driveline balance.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f0502A06" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figDE1/DE1617A.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         scalefitheight="232px"/>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Disconnect the driveshaft at the axle.</para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f0502A07" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../fign00/N0020369.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         scalefitheight="232px"/>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Remove and discard the U-joint retaining bolts.</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Remove and discard the U-joint retaining straps.
                        <callout2 type="alpha">Using mechanic's wire, position aside and support the driveshaft.
                        </callout2>
                    </callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Loosen the pinion nut if drive pinion disassembly is necessary.</para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f0502A08" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figDE1/DE1892A.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         scalefitheight="232px"/>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the axle shafts. For additional information, refer to
                    <hotlnk document="s14020_X2050219.xml" xrefid="x2050219">Wheel Hubs and Bearings</hotlnk>.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove all but the 2 top carrier-to-axle housing retaining bolts, noting the length and
                    position of each bolt.
                </para>
                <para>&#8226; Discard the differential carrier housing bolts.</para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f0502A09" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figDE1/DE1893A.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         scalefitheight="232px"/>
            </figure>
            <specpara>
                <warning>
                    <para>Secure the differential carrier to the jack to prevent it from falling when removing it from
                        the axle housing. Failure to follow these instructions may result in personal injury.
                    </para>
                </warning>
            </specpara>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the differential carrier from the axle housing.</para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f0502A10" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../fign00/N0020637.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         scalefitheight="232px"/>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Position a suitable jack under the differential carrier.</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Remove and discard the remaining retaining bolts.</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Use the slots to separate the differential carrier approximately 25.4-50.8
                        mm (1-2 inches) from the axle housing.
                    </callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Secure the differential carrier to a suitable jack, and remove the
                        differential carrier from the axle housing.
                    </callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <specpara>
                <caution>
                    <para>Alkaline cleaning solutions will damage machine surfaces. Use only emulsion cleaners or
                        petroleum-based cleaning solvent.
                    </para>
                </caution>
            </specpara>
            <specpara>
                <caution>
                    <para>Use only soft, clean, lintless towels to dry the components.</para>
                </caution>
            </specpara>
            <specpara>
                <caution>
                    <para>After drying, lightly coat the components with rust inhibitor or clean lubricant to prevent
                        damage from corrosion. Wrap all components that are going to be in storage for a prolonged
                        period in wax paper.
                    </para>
                </caution>
            </specpara>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Clean and dry the components as necessary.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Inspect the gear set for pitting, scoring, wear and damage.</para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f0502A11" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figa00/A0080113.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         scalefitheight="232px"/>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Inspect the splines for wear, cracking and distortion from twisting.</para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f0502A12" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figDE1/DE1896A.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         scalefitheight="232px"/>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Inspect the axle flange O-ring.</para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f0502A13" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figDE1/DE1977A.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         scalefitheight="232px"/>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Clean the axle housing interior, the axle and differential carrier housing sealing
                    surfaces and the differential carrier mounting bolt hole threads. Inspect the housing for stripped
                    and damaged threads and bending fatigue.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f0502A14" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figa00/A0062509.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         scalefitheight="232px"/>
            </figure>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Differential Carrier Installation</title>
            <specpara>
                <caution>
                    <para>The gasket material must cure for one hour before filling the axle with lubricant.</para>
                </caution>
            </specpara>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Apply a continuous bead of Gasket Maker onto the axle housing mounting flange and around
                    each bolt hole.
                </para>
                <para>&#8226; Use Gasket Maker or equivalent.</para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f0502A15" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figDE1/DE1898A.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         scalefitheight="232px"/>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Thread 2 studs into the axle housing. This will eliminate rotation of the differential
                    carrier assembly after it makes contact with the gasket material.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f0502A16" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figa00/A0062248.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         scalefitheight="232px"/>
            </figure>
            <specpara>
                <warning>
                    <para>Secure the differential carrier to the jack to prevent it from falling. Failure to follow
                        these instructions may result in personal injury.
                    </para>
                </warning>
            </specpara>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Position the differential carrier into the axle housing, using the 2 studs to align the
                    differential carrier and housing.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f0502A17" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figDE1/DE1900A.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         scalefitheight="232px"/>
            </figure>
            <specpara>
                <caution>
                    <para>Make sure the bolt threads are clean.</para>
                </caution>
            </specpara>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install new differential carrier housing bolts.</para>
                <randlist type="bullet">
                    <item>
                        <para>Remove the 2 alignment studs only after installing several of the bolts.</para>
                    </item>
                    <item>
                        <para>Tighten the bolts in a cross pattern.</para>
                    </item>
                    <item>
                        <para>Tighten to 203 Nm (150 lb-ft).</para>
                    </item>
                </randlist>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f0502A18" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figDE1/DE1893A.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         scalefitheight="232px"/>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install the axle shafts. For additional information, refer to
                    <hotlnk document="s14020_X2050219.xml" xrefid="x2050219">Wheel Hubs and Bearings</hotlnk>.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f0502A19" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figDE1/DE1976A.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         scalefitheight="232px"/>
            </figure>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>Align the index marks made during removal.</para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Connect the driveshaft at the axle.</para>
                <randlist type="bullet">
                    <item>
                        <para>Install new U-joint retaining straps and new U-joint retaining bolts.</para>
                    </item>
                    <item>
                        <para>Tighten to 74 Nm (55 lb-ft).</para>
                    </item>
                </randlist>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f0502A20" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../fign00/N0020391.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         scalefitheight="232px"/>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Connect the rear anti-lock brake sensor electrical connector, if equipped.</para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f0502A21" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figDE1/DE1891A.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         scalefitheight="232px"/>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the fill plug.</para>
            </step1>
            <specpara>
                <caution>
                    <para>A lubricant level close enough to the bottom of the fill hole to be seen or touched is not
                        sufficient. The lubricant must be level with the fill hole.
                    </para>
                </caution>
            </specpara>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Fill the axle with lubricant until the lubricant is level with the fill hole.</para>
                <para>&#8226; Use SAE 75W-140 High Performance Rear Axle Lubricant or equivalent.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Clean and install the fill plug.</para>
                <para>&#8226; Tighten to 54 Nm (40 lb-ft).</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the wheel chocks.</para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f0502A22" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figDE1/DE1889A.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         scalefitheight="232px"/>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Release the parking brake.</para>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
    </svcproc>
